Clairement pas. The creature merely whistled and tried to charge straight at Thassalin. Fortunately, despite its size, he was sufficiently agile to dodge, but Nyssi couldn't help but scream when she almost lost her grip on his scales that were too smooth.
"HOW DO YOU KILL THEM ?", shouted Nyssi.
"GO FOR THEIR HEADS !"
"THAT'S NOT GOING TO BE EASY !"
Thassalin blew out air, then circled around to approach the mountain he called home. The black beast followed, becoming somewhat alarmed when a fire bolt struck it from behind. The creature hadn't noticed it wasn't alone anymore. Its alarm grew when Thassalin slowed down, then hit it violently on the head with his tail, making it deviate from its trajectory.
Grumbling and whistling, the creature took to the air and spat into the sky. Suddenly, everything turned black, as if the monster was sucking up the light of the sky and replacing it with a perpetual cloud of night.
With no visibility left, Thassalin tried to retreat, but brushed against the treetops before crashing into the clearing. As if she knew exactly where he had fallen, the creature charged straight at him, dragging the dark cloud behind it.
"Kayel !", exclaimed Tenuk as he extricated himself from the cloud and began to circle in the air, trying to spot Nyssi and Thassalin below in the darkness. "What do we do, Kayel ? Kayel... ? Kayel, where are you ?"
Below, Nyssi struggled to get up. She was sure she had broken something, but her strange healing powers, far from natural, had already begun to take effect. This could not be said for Thassalin, who lay on a hillock, propped up against the only tree that had not bent under his weight. Nyssi did her best to try and reach Thassalin, but she could not see two meters in front of her. Everything was plunged into darkness, engulfed in the unholy shadows. And in those shadows, something was screaming.
An awful whip-like tail fell beside Nyssi, knocking her over. However, she noticed that the tail was thrashing around, not aiming at her. From what Nyssi could see and hear of the creature, it was growling and scratching the shadows it had created. Something was teleporting through the darkness, striking the monster, disorienting it.
A sudden gunshot rang out, and the monster collapsed silently, lifeless. The darkness surrounding them dissipated, revealing what had happened. Standing on top of the creature was Kayel, holding a rifle and panting.
"It's... the oddest shadow leap I've ever made... Thanto kat'olon...", gasped Kayel. His eyes glowed with a black light, and a dark energy coursed through his body. However, as he spoke, Kayel's organic plating regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow hue.
Nyssi took a moment to understand what had occurred. They all knew that Kayel possessed strange powers of darkness. He rarely used them, as most people considered them improper and rather terrifying. But Nyssi did not know that Kayel could use these powers in the dark. And, judging by his behavior, Kayel seemed quite surprised as well.
"Are you okay ?", Nyssi couldn't help but ask.
"Yes, I'm fine. I killed something. It'll feel better in a minute." Kayel examined his work, while Tenuk made his way to land beside him, returning to his normal Spast form.
Now that the creature was no longer moving, they could better see what it was. Its skin was black as coal and sticky, but the saliva continued to adhere to its body. It had four wings and four limbs, all ending in long claws, and two straight horns protruded from its skull.
Barely had Tenuk and Kayel asked what this thing was when something howled and leaped out of a nearby bush. However, the beast did not have time to reach them, as a familiar vehicle crashed into its flank, sending it sprawling at the feet of Nyssi. Taking no chances, she grabbed her rifle and immediately shot it in the head, killing the creature on the spot.
"Oops...," muttered Retvik from the driver's seat, before clumsily shutting off the engine and hopping out of the truck. "I, uh, didn't mean to do that. Are you all right?"
"You almost missed all the action," regretted Tenuk. "Where were you?"
"You all dropped me. I came here as fast as I could," sighed Retvik. "Can someone tell me what these abominations are?"
The questioning of Retvik received a happy response from Thassalin, who had just gotten up. He was cut and scratched all over and seemed a bit disoriented, but he didn't look too injured.
"YOU KILLED THE CORRUPTIDS! THE INFECTED MONSTERS. CREATURES LEFT HERE WHEN THE CORRUPTION ATTACKED YOUR GODS."
"You mean... the horrible god-monster that we... helped kill?" stammered Tenuk.
"YES. ABSOLUTELY. THERE MIGHT BE OTHERS, BUT I DIDN'T SUCCEED IN HITTING THEIR HEADS. I'M MISSING A RIFLE. PLUS, TWO AGAINST ONE IS NOT FAIR, RIGHT?" Thassalin walked towards Kayel and patted his head. "THANK YOU, MY BOY. YOU REMIND ME OF MY OLD FRIEND ARKADIN. BUT LESS DEADLY AND LESS ABLE TO KILL ENTIRE UNIVERSES."
"Uh... thank you... I suppose," said Kayel with a shrug. "So, we're done here, then?"
Nissy shrugged, then grabbed her camera to photograph the now decidedly dead creatures. She then took out her favorite dagger, the Death God's dagger, and began cutting one of the creature's horns, before moving on to the other. But as she finished, the creatures flared up and rapidly turned into piles of ashes. The same thing happened to the horns Nyssi had cut.
"Well... it's both convenient and not at all convenient," she sighed. "At least I have the photos..."
